reviews_data.review_text: I have a problem with BOTH the library system, the government & GOOGLE! Unfortunately US taxpayers can NOT trust any of them? Online it says they are open, at the location their hours say they are open on Sunday? However they are CLOSED? What kind of bureaucrat MAKES these decisions? Then DOES NOT Bother to inform the public?!
Nice people by the front desk, very helpful! Thank you!

I notice a lot of the libraries these days focus more on discriminating against library patrons. Then encouraging all individuals from all walks of life to embrace the fundamentals of learning and reading books. It's like they only want certain individuals (class & race) in the library. It so discriminating and it is so annoying that it interferes with individuals using the library to work on their work. If that's the case then individuals who can't accept all individuals from all walks of life need to work in another field than the library. Because you do have to be able to provide service to all library patrons from all walks of life and all classes. You can't be selective or discriminating with the public. Because it is open to everybody who wants to use and needs to use it. Do better and more nonjudgmental. BE THE CHANGE YOU SEEK IN THE WORLD.

reviews_data.review_text:
The staff and resources make the difference.
They have the best exhibits, workshops, and partnerships with local community leaders. My children basically grew up there. From teaching them that public nursing is okay and legal to hosting NC Shero's there - BFR regional is the place to be.
Of course easy, adequate parking is a win too.
I really enjoy going to this library. They have a lot of activities for children and the staff are polite and always willing to help their consumers.
Voting
A very nice library nice and clean clean parking lot friendly staff professional people working there I highly recommend this library for you and your family
Everyone was very sweet.  They have designated areas for different age groups and even computers for the kids. They offer story time and other activities for kids.
Very nice and quiet library to do business
Love, Love this Place! When I want to escape.. This is where I go...

This is a decent-sized quiet library. I know you shouldn't even have to write quiet when explaining a library, but it's been my experience that not all libraries in Charlotte are quiet. They have story time available for toddlers and babies. Not as many toys for kids but they do have tons of computers which stay available most of the morning. They have a lot of Spanish children's books and tons of picture books. I was really happy to see that they have a room for nursing mothers, and a family bathroom.  My kids really loved it here. As far as the selection and adults I only went through non fictions which word decent lots of new books and well kept. Lots of computers in the internet lab. It seems like they have a really large community room although it was being a news for early voting. Due to the fact they had early voting going on parking was really hard to find. Other than that my run-ins with the staff were nice they were well knowledge and very helpful. They have a patio available although it was not open and I'm not sure if it's always closed or just happened to be closed today. I'm happy to have found it can't wait to go back!
I live in Dalebrook. This library is very assessible but people during use of computers can be unprofessionally rude.
Friendly staff, clean, decent young adult book section.
Always nice

This library is the nicest building within several surrounding blocks, this isn't located in the best neighborhood. On the bus line. Decent sized parking lot. There is a guard posted outside for safety. Huge computer lab. Staff is friendly.

Nice size library with computer lab, meeting room and children's section.
Kids section:
Good selection of books
Good selection of DVDs
Six kids computers
Play area with rug, blocks, foam letters and
puzzles
Rocking chairs
Table area where they put out crayons and
Paper
Story time is fine. Librarians are good about
Letting kids be kids and don't try and keep
them still.
I love this library. People are always so helpful. Never had a bad experience here!
Great place to be with your kids or on your own. The staff are exceptional always so helpful.
The staff there are great and always courteous and helpful!!!!!!
Small but relatively well stocked as far as Charlotte goes.

This was my childhood library! I always and only really knew of it so it's a comfortable place. (Even for someone so shy...!) The book supply is nice (excluding a variety of manga, like most places in the U.S.) but overall it's a great place. They've been initiating programs (for kids, teens, and adults!) and brought in new technology; which took away from the original comfort, but is helpful to those who need it! I recommend this library for people who want to be comfortable when they work! There are these 'quiet rooms' that kind of block out sound! It's a small library, I think (having only one other one to compare it to.. kind of!). It's nice.
It's great I love it ... but don't be late the fines can add up.  Gssh
